This is called a aligned environment. Here we have two lines of equal width, with the second line starting immediately below the first line. The lines are separated by an `aligned` environment.
The number of lines in the second line can be any positive integer greater than 0. This is typically used when you want to introduce some commentary or additional information that helps explain the equation.
