Answer: Instead of a footnote use a "comment" (see section \texttt{\ref{sect:comment}} below).

To add a comment at the end of the paragraph, you can use the ``at sign" $@$ following the last punctuation mark. This will place the comment after the paragraph. If you want the comment before the paragraph, precede the $@$ with the backslash escape character: $\backslash @$.

In your case, add the comment \textbf{Note} after the item c and before the period (if any):
\begin{itemize}
  \item [c] \textbf{Item C}
  \textbf{Note}
  \item [d] \textbf{Item D}
\end{itemize}
If you prefer to have the comment after the items, use the backslash escape character:
\begin{itemize}
  \item [c] \textbf{Item C}
  @\textbf{Note}
  \item [d] \textbf{Item D}
\end{itemize}
